# .syncignore — repositories to skip when running sync-github-repos.sh
#
# Copy this file to ".syncignore" (same directory as the script) and list the
# repositories you do NOT want cloned or updated. Matched repos are skipped
# entirely; any existing local clone is left on disk untouched.
#
# Rules:
#   - One glob pattern per line, matched against "owner/repo".
#   - '*' matches any run of characters, '?' matches a single character.
#   - Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
#   - Trailing '# comments' on a pattern line are stripped too.
#
# Examples:
#   octocat/Hello-World      # one specific repo
#   myorg/*                  # every repo under an owner/org
#   */secret-*               # any repo whose name starts with "secret-"
#   *-fork                   # any repo whose name ends with "-fork"
#
# Note: your real .syncignore is gitignored, so private repo names you put in
# it stay local and are never committed.
